Episodes.Title: The Beginning of the End
Episodes.Plot: The "TGS" gang returning from hiatus, only to be shocked by Jack's awful fall programming lineup. Meanwhile, bridezilla Jenna taps Liz to be her maid of honor, and Tracy is invited to a dinner party by Kenneth and Hazel.

Episodes.Title: Governor Dunston
Episodes.Plot: Jack and Liz find themselves at odds over political satire at "TGS". Criss and Liz make a surprising relationship breakthrough. Meanwhile, Jenna, discouraged by the disappointing sales of her summer dance hit, is thrilled to learn that Kenneth's mother and her boyfriend still buy music.

Episodes.Title: Stride of Pride
Episodes.Plot: Liz works to prove to Tracy that women are funny while simultaneously attempting to head off a meltdown from Jenna after some negative publicity. Jack tries out an unconventional dating strategy.

Episodes.Title: Unwindulax
Episodes.Plot: Liz and Jack find themselves battling to influence voters in the upcoming presidential election. Meanwhile, as Jenna goes to great lengths to please her new fan base, the writers seek out new ways to mess with her.

Episodes.Title: There's No I in America
Episodes.Plot: Realizing that Jenna could decide the Presidential election, Liz and Jack stage a debate to win her support and her followers. Kenneth turns to Tracy for advice on how to be an informed voter, while Pete tries to recreate the magic of the 2008 election.

Episodes.Title: Aunt Phatso vs. Jack Donaghy
Episodes.Plot: Tracy and Jack engage in a battle of wits after Tracy depicts Jack as a villain in his latest project. On Jack's advice, Liz puts her own needs ahead of those of "TGS." Meanwhile, Jenna tries to shield Kenneth from Hazel's manipulation but her own selfishness gets in the way.

Episodes.Title: Mazel Tov, Dummies!
Episodes.Plot: After an encounter with Dennis Duffy, Liz and Criss decide to take drastic measures to start a family. As Liz looks toward the future, Jack and Jenna evaluate their own self-worth, and Tracy laments a shocking medical diagnosis.

Episodes.Title: My Whole Life is Thunder
Episodes.Plot: Jenna annoys Liz with her wedding envy, Jack devises a plan to avoid disappointing his visiting mother and Tracy attempts to cheer up Kenneth.

Episodes.Title: Game Over
Episodes.Plot: Jack asks Devin Banks to help him discredit Kaylie Hooper, Jack's teenage nemesis and KableTown's future CEO. Liz considers her options as she tries to become a mother. Tracy directs Octavia Spencer in his movie.

Episodes.Title: Florida
Episodes.Plot: When Jack persuades Liz to go to Florida with him, they make a shocking discovery about his mother. Jenna and Tracy assume responsibility for the show in Liz's absence, resulting in disaster for Kenneth.

Episodes.Title: A Goon's Deed in a Weary World
Episodes.Plot: As her new kids arrive, Liz scrambles to save TGS from cancellation. Jack finds a new NBC president.

Episodes.Title: Hogcock!
Episodes.Plot: Liz has trouble adjusting to being a stay-at-home mother. Jack takes stock of his life, and Tracy struggles to get on without Kenneth.

Episodes.Title: Last Lunch
Episodes.Plot: The gang reunites for one final episode of TGS.
